# Rust / Cargo
target/

# Models
models/
!/models/README.md
*.onnx

# Fixtures
# Image/opencv fixtures are kept local — they can contain sensitive faces
# (see fixtures/README.md), so they are intentionally not committed. Only the
# README and the synthetic golden data are tracked. Using `fixtures/*` (not
# `fixtures/`) lets git descend into the re-included subdir.
fixtures/*
!/fixtures/README.md
!/fixtures/golden/

# IDEs / Editors
.claude/
.codex
.idea/

# Logs and Caches
*.log
cache/

# Misc / Local
# Anchored to the repo root so crate-level `tests/` directories (e.g.
# fcs-core/tests/) stay tracked; only a root-level scratch dir is ignored.
/benchmarks/
nul
out.json
/scripts/
/tests/

